-- Aqua America Spends $12 Million on First-Half 2013 Acquisitions
-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m
-- 2013-07-01T15:42:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-01/aqua-america-spends-12-million-on-first-half-2013-acquisitions.html
Aqua America Inc. (WTR) , the second-largest
water utility in the U.S. by market value, spent more than $12
million on seven acquisitions in the first six months of this
year.  The utility purchased systems in Pennsylvania, North
Carolina and Virginia, according to a statement today from Bryn
Mawr, Pennsylvania-based Aqua America. The utility serves about
3 million residents in nine states.  “Our growth-through-acquisition strategy is continuing to
fill in our footprint in key growth areas,” Aqua America Chief
Executive Officer Nicholas DeBenedictis said in the statement.  American Water Works Co. is the largest U.S. water utility.  To contact the reporter on this story:
